{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"WWDC20","title":"Meet Scribble for iPad","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"kind":"article","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10106-Meet-Scribble-for-iPad"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (14 min)","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc20\/10106"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"Writing-experience","type":"heading","text":"Writing experience","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can write directly on a text field without the need to select the field first.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can draw a horizontal line to select text and perform the normal text editing actions."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also scratch out some text that you want to delete.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Scribble-Supporting-APIs","type":"heading","text":"Scribble Supporting APIs","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scribble relies on standard Text controls\/inputs ("},{"code":"UITextField","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"UITextView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", …)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scribble does not support password fields (because Apple’s recommended way to input password is via auto fill)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"for custom UI elements Scribble relies on UIKit’s text input protocols ("},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uitextinput","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uikeyinput","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uitextinputtraits","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uitextinteraction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"New-APIs","type":"heading","text":"New APIs","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Scribble introduces two interactions, ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiscribbleinteraction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uiindirectscribbleinteraction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", which are used to customize the behavior of Scribble in your app.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both interactions are added to views where the custom behavior takes place.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"UIScribbleInteraction","type":"heading","text":"UIScribbleInteraction","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The interaction has a delegate, and this delegate is where an app can customize the Scribble experience, for example:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"disabling Scribble on the view","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"delaying that view from becoming first responder until handwriting has momentarily paused"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"being informed when Scribble handwriting begins or ends"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"ty